FNB has revealed changes to its banking fees and eBucks rewards programme. The changes will come into effect on 1 July 2018. “The key highlights include eWallet eXtra officially becoming the most affordable entry-level bank account with no monthly fees,” said Raj Makanjee, FNB Retail CEO. The inclusion of the recent 15% VAT fee hike will also be implemented as part of the changes. Major changes to FNB’s account fees and eBucks structure are highlighted below.